`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `observe(gameState$, listener)` in Legend State fires **synchronously** when any child observable changes — this is the "reactive graph" model. No microtask/Promise needed in tests.
- `subscribe()` in the store wraps `observe` to give a Zustand-compatible API. The returned function is the unsubscriber (calls `dispose` under the hood).
- Testing auto-save trigger means verifying the subscription fires on state mutation — which is all auto-save needs: "state changed → listener → save".
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
